\nwaves of bulge formation are not only distinguishable in terms of stellar ages,\nbut also in star formation mode. All 1$^{\\rm st}$-wave bulges formed fast at\n$z\\sim6$, with typical timescales around 200 Myr. A significant fraction of the\n2$^{\\rm{nd}}$-wave bulges assembled more slowly, with star formation timescales\nas long as 1 Gyr. The results of this work suggest that the centers of massive\ndisk-like galaxies actually harbor the oldest spheroids formed in the Universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Mar 2021 18:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-09"}
