 on\ntimescales of millions of years. Such mechanisms include a trap formed by a\nvery close-in extra planet or the inner edge of a dead zone. The low spectral\nindex of the disk around CIDA1 is difficult to explain and challenges our\ncurrent dust evolution models, in particular processes like fragmentation,\ngrowth, and diffusion of particles inside pressure bumps.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Mar 2021 18:25:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Apr 2021 08:54:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-02"}
